To make up the difference, the House Democratic source said the Pentagon is expected to draw upon its military construction budget.
Delaying billions of construction projects could invite its own host of problems.
To reprogram funds from one division of DOD, like military construction, to another pot requires direct approval from senior lawmakers of both parties.